title: Understanding Tables
text: A table is a structured format for organizing data, typically in rows and columns. It is a fundamental concept in databases and spreadsheets.

title: Characteristics of a Table
text: Tables are often used to store data in a way that is easy to read and manipulate. They are two-dimensional, meaning they have both rows and columns.

title: Identifying the Unique Feature
text: What makes a table distinct from other data organization methods?
